-- Argentine Stocks: Petrobras Argentina, Tenaris and Polledo
-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 2012-03-06T16:09:35Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-06/argentine-stocks-petrobras-argentina-tenaris-and-polledo.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Argentine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 12:58 p.m. in Buenos
Aires.  The  Merval (MERVAL)  Index fell 2.1 percent to 2,633.84.  Petrobras Argentina SA (PESA)   dropped 5.4 percent, the
most in 18 weeks, to 6.52 pesos. The local unit of  Brazil ’s
state-controlled oil company Petroleo Brasileiro SA is falling
on speculation that a conflict between  YPF SA (YPFD) , Argentina’s
largest energy company, and the government may affect other
fuel-distribution companies, Adrian Mayoral, a trader and
analyst at Buenos Aires-based brokerage Mayoral Bursatil, said
in a phone interview.  Polledo SA (POLL)   advanced 5.8 percent to 0.201 pesos.
The Argentine construction company has increased 12 percent in
the last two days after it reached an agreement to restructure
17.5 million pesos ($4 million) in debt. It announced the
agreement in a statement posted yesterday on the website of the
Buenos Aires stock exchange.  Tenaris SA (TEN)   retreated for second day, dropping 3.6
percent to 93.8 pesos. The world’s largest producer of seamless
steel tubes used in the oil industry fell in line with the price
of crude oil.  To contact the reporter on this story:
